  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reducing Gender Inequalities in Agriculture in Central America</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Nicaragua, Lutheran World Relief (LWR), the Asociaci&#xF3;n para la Diversificaci&#xF3;n y el Desarrollo Agr&#xED;cola Comunal (ADDAC), and the cooperative Flor de Pancasan, with technical support from gender experts at Cultural Practice LLC., came together in 2013 to develop and pilot tools for identifying and integrating gender equitable business incentives within the cooperative and member households as a way to improve production and income at both levels. This ongoing project, entitled Learning for Gender Integration (LGI) in Nicaragua, has helped farmers measure the positive impacts on productivity and has led to the implementation of best practices in gender integration by male and female members. 
Through the Reducing Gender Inequalities in Agriculture in Central America project, LWR will further validate, refine and document its LGI model of helping cooperatives reveal business incentives for reducing gender inequalities at the cooperative and household level.</narrative>
  </description>
